Description: Fix CVE-2024-21534 - RCE via JSONPath script-expression sandbox escape
 The JSONPath script-expression filter evaluator (`[?(...)]` and `[(...)]`) compiled
 user-controlled JavaScript via Node's `vm` module (node path) and `new Function(...)`
 (browser path) without prototype hardening. An attacker could escape the sandbox
 via `[].constructor.constructor("...")` to reach the host `Function` constructor
 and from there `this.process.mainModule.require("child_process").execSync(...)`,
 yielding arbitrary remote code execution.
 .
 The upstream fix (commit 73ad72e, released in v10.2.0) hardens a jsep-AST-based
 evaluator (`src/Safe-Script.js`) which does not exist in v7.2.0. This backport
 re-implements the protective intent for v7.2.0's two distinct evaluation paths:
 .
   * A shared denylist (`_$_assertSafeScript`) in `src/jsonpath.js` rejects any
     script text containing tokens that enable VM/sandbox escape: `constructor`,
     `__proto__`, `__defineGetter__`, `__defineSetter__`, `Function`, `process`,
     `globalThis`, `global`, `require`, `import`. The denylist is invoked from
     `_eval` before the script is compiled or cached.
   * `src/jsonpath-node.js` now wraps Node's `vm` module so `runInNewContext` is
     called with a prototype-less context (`Object.assign(Object.create(null), ctx)`)
     and re-applies the denylist as defence-in-depth.
   * `src/jsonpath-browser.js` re-applies the denylist at the entry of
     `runInNewContext` so the in-browser `new Function(...)` path is also blocked.
 .
 The denylist is intentionally narrow: ordinary JSONPath filter expressions
 (e.g. `$[?(@.price < 10)]`, `$..book[?(@.author === "Tolkien")]`) remain
 functional. Only adversarial expressions that reference the dangerous identifiers
 above are rejected with a `ReferenceError`.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/JSONPath-Plus/JSONPath/commit/73ad72e5ee788d8287dea6e8283a3f16f63c9eb8
Bug: https://github.com/JSONPath-Plus/JSONPath/issues/226
Bug-CVE: CVE-2024-21534
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-28

